# Idolatry Verses in the Book of Genesis (NRSV and LSV)

## Genesis 31:19

**NRSV:**
> "Laban had gone to shear his sheep, and Rachel stole her father's household gods."

**LSV:**
> "And Laban has gone to shear his flock, and Rachel steals the teraphim which her father has."

## Genesis 35:2-4

**NRSV:**
> "So Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him, 'Put away the foreign gods that are among you, and purify yourselves, and change your clothes; then come, let us go up to Bethel, that I may make an altar there to the God who answered me in the day of my distress and has been with me wherever I have gone.' So they gave to Jacob all the foreign gods that they had, and the rings that were in their ears; and Jacob hid them under the oak that was near Shechem."

**LSV:**
> "And Jacob says to his household, and to all who [are] with him, 'Turn aside the gods of the stranger which [are] in your midst, and cleanse yourselves, and change your garments, and we rise, and go up to Bethel, and I make there an altar to God, who answered me in the day of my distress, and is with me in the way that I have gone.' And they give to Jacob all the gods of the stranger that [are] in their hand, and the earrings that [are] in their ears, and Jacob hides them under the oak which [is] by Shechem."
